      "Good long-term option if Core Web Vitals or traffic volume require more control",
      "Can support redirects, headers and deployment previews"
    ],
    "cloudflarePagesCons": [
      "Migration usually touches DNS/nameserver or records, creating email-record risk if rushed",
      "Requires careful preservation of MX, mail A, SPF, DKIM and DMARC records",
      "Adds migration complexity while indexing is just starting"
    ],
    "netlifyPros": [
      "Simple static hosting with deploy previews, redirects and headers",
      "Good operational controls for static SEO sites",
      "Can be adopted later without redesigning the site"
    ],
    "netlifyCons": [
      "May require DNS changes or custom-domain reconfiguration",
      "Free-tier bandwidth/build limits should be watched as traffic grows",
      "Less compelling than Cloudflare Pages if the main future need is edge caching and DNS integration"
    ],
    "dnsEmailRisksIfMigrating": [
      "Mail can break if MX, mail A, SPF, DKIM or DMARC records are missed during DNS/provider changes",
      "A rushed nameserver move can temporarily affect both website and email resolution",
      "Migration should use a written DNS inventory, low TTL window and rollback plan"
    ],
